Type II: Exercise 7B
Directions: The questions below consist of a question followed by two statements labeled I and II. You have to decide if these statements are sufficient to answer the question. Give answer
1) If statement I alone is sufficient to answer the question but statement II alone is not sufficient to answer the question;
2) If statement II alone is sufficient to answer the question but statement I alone is not sufficient to answer the question;
3) If you can get the answer from I and II together although neither statement suffices by itself;
4) If statement I alone is sufficient and statement II alone is sufficient; and
5) If you cannot get the answer from statements I and II together but still more data are needed.
